Alfred Thomas Davies (1881–1941) was Conservative MP for Lincoln (UK Parliament constituency).
He was first elected in 1918 with the Coalition Coupon as a supporter of the government, unseating the Liberal incumbent Charles Roberts.
He stood down in 1924.
